This objective motivates me greatly to support and work on innovative research, to apply the results in commercial projects and to a advise the Dutch ministry of Economic Affairs & Climate on related policy questions. 

Currently I am working on several studies to investigate the technical feasibility of storing hydrogen in natural gas fields. Integrated energy system modelling shows that the growing contribution of renewable energy to the Dutch energy mix will require significant storage capacity to compensate for fluctuating electricity production from wind and solar energy. A possible solution is to store energy as hydrogen in the subsurface. 

EBN is developing projects to store CO2 in offshore depleted gas fields. My involvement regarding this topic is helping to understand and predict the technical challenges concerning the flow of CO2. Besides that I am involved in strategically optimizing the re-use of existing Dutch infrastructure portfolio (gas fields, pipelines, production platforms, etc..) with the aim to store larges quantities of CO2 for the lowest cost to the society.
